==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shag
<hw>Shag</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>sceacga</ets> a
bush of hair; akin to Icel. <ets>skegg</ets> the beard, Sw.
<ets>sk⟦aum⟧gg</ets>, Dan. <ets>skj<?/g</ets>. Cf. <er>Schock</er> of
hair.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Coarse hair or nap; rough, woolly
hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>True Witney broadcloth, with its <qex>shag</qex> unshorn.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cloth having a long, coarse nap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>A kind of prepared tobacco cut
fine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of
cormorant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shag</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shag
<hw>Shag</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Hairy; shaggy.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shag</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shag
<hw>Shag</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Shagged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Shagging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make hairy or shaggy; hence,
to make rough.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Shag</qex> the green zone that bounds the boreal skies.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Barlow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- (Sport) To chase, as (a) to chase and return balls hit out of
bounds. (b) (Baseball) to catch fly balls for practise. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shagbark</ent>⟦br⟧
